If you have questions please let me know.
Blake Wentz
Sent from my iPhone

helpdesk-note.body:
Blake,
Mapped drives are done at sign-on to Windows and are given permissions based on the username. I believe the device also needs to be a member of the domain for this to work at logon. Are the students logging into the iPlan tables at boot, or does it use a generic name? I'm not sure we can give M and O access to a generic username. I'll talk to the sysadmin (he's on vacation till Monday) and see if there's some way we can grant limited access without having to have individual users sign in. Are there particular folders on M and O that the students will need?
Let me know,

helpdesk-ticket.subject: wireless access in L 331
helpdesk-ticket.description: I believe new wireless access points have been installed in the Library building, but I'm still seeing very poor connectivity in my office. I was unable to connect a new Linux computer to MSOE in my office last week, but as soon as I moved to a different location the connection was established very quickly. I and my students have also had problems connecting the school laptop. When I use the Wi-fi Analyzer app, the MSOE network rises above -70 dB for only short time periods. Note this is in my office - connectivity in the hallway just outside my office is fine because of the WAP at the other end. Interestingly, I and my students can generally always connect to MSOE-Guest in my office; one person suggested maybe one of the WAPs in the area is configured to broadcast that network only. In any case, this lack of connectivity makes it difficult for me and my students to work with devices that do not support wired network access.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Blackboard, my course is missing

In past years the course just showed up. Is this a mistake, or have we changed how Blackboard is used such that I have to create it myself in some manner (and if so, how)?
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Not sure if this is the right venue for this question:
I logged into Blackboard to start posting my students grades, but my current course (CE-2800) that I am teaching is not listed.  In past years the course just showed up.  Is this a mistake, or have we changed how Blackboard is used such that I have to create it myself in some manner (and if so, how)?

helpdesk-note.body: Is it an automatic process or is there something he is supposed to do on his end?
helpdesk-note.body-html: Is it an automatic process or is there something he is supposed to do on his end?

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Mark,
I don't think that anything has changed much. I looked in through the admin page, and I can see your course and that you are listed as the instructor. It's currently "Unavailable to the students", but you should see it on your list of courses. I added the words "Fall 2015-16" to the end of the title. Sometimes things don't get listed in any particular order, so it ends up in the middle of your list. Let me know if you can see the section with this extension on the name. Pat Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/1611 Not sure if this is the right venue for this question: I logged into Blackboard to start posting my students grades, but my current course (CE-2800) that I am teaching is not listed. In past years the course just showed up. Is this a mistake, or have we changed how Blackboard is used such that I have to create it myself in some manner (and if so, how)?
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Mark,

I don't think that anything has changed much. I looked in through the admin page, and I can see your course and that you are listed as the instructor.  It's currently "Unavailable to the students", but you should see it on your list of courses.  I added the words "Fall 2015-16" to the end of the title. Sometimes things don't get listed in any particular order, so it ends up in the middle of your list.  Let me know if you can see the section with this extension on the name.
Pat

Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/1611
Not sure if this is the right venue for this question:
I logged into Blackboard to start posting my students grades, but my current course (CE-2800) that I am teaching is not listed.  In past years the course just showed up.  Is this a mistake, or have we changed how Blackboard is used such that I have to create it myself in some manner (and if so, how)?

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Abby, I think that the courses are not always listed in a logical sequence, and they all have the same "course name" (different ID, but the same generic names). I added "fall 2015-16" to the end of that particular course name, so hopefully it will stand out for him now.
I don't think that anything at all has "changed". It's just sometimes hard to find if they have taught multiple sections of the same course over time.
I did send him a response - this is just FYI :)

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Sean Moen, Give this a shot and please let the helpdesk know how it goes:
Teredo is an IPv4 to IPv6 conversion protocol. However, our network, while capable of IPv6, does not currently route IPv6 traffic. This would require setting up all new DHCP subnets, and rewriting each firewall rule for both IPv4 and IPv6 objects. However, IPv6 by design will always fail back to IPv4 when it cannot establish a connection. While Xbox One users will not be able to get rid of the error message "Cannot Get a Teredo IP Address", they should still be able to use their XBO and XBL normally, and join/chat in multiplayers games. Some things they can try to correct a "Strict NAT" issue: Recommend they add the XBO to the DMZ on their router, if they have one that allows DMZ addresses Enable UPNP to allow necessary ports to be available to the XBO (may require router and XBO reboot) Open the following ports (either do this or enable UPNP, not both): Port 88 (UDP) Port 3074 (UDP and TCP) Port 53 (UDP and TCP) Port 80 (TCP) Port 500 (UDP) UDP Port 3544 (UDP) UDP Port 4500 (UDP) Reset the MAC address of the XBO: Settings > network > Advanced settings > Alternate mac address > Clear
Peter Pfister Help Desk Coordinator 414.277.7202
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Sean Moen,
Give this a shot and please let the helpdesk know how it goes:

Teredo is an IPv4 to IPv6 conversion protocol. However, our network, while capable of IPv6, does not currently route IPv6 traffic. This would require setting up all new DHCP subnets, and rewriting each firewall rule for both IPv4 and IPv6 objects.
However, IPv6 by design will always fail back to IPv4 when it cannot establish a connection. While Xbox One users will not be able to get rid of the error message "Cannot Get a Teredo IP Address", they should still be able to use their XBO and XBL normally, and join/chat in multiplayers games.
Some things they can try to correct a "Strict NAT" issue:
Recommend they add the XBO to the DMZ on their router, if they have one that allows DMZ addresses
Enable UPNP to allow necessary ports to be available to the XBO (may require router and XBO reboot)
Open the following ports (either do this or enable UPNP, not both):
Port 88 (UDP)
Port 3074 (UDP and TCP)
Port 53 (UDP and TCP)
Port 80 (TCP)
Port 500 (UDP)
UDP Port 3544 (UDP)
UDP Port 4500 (UDP)
Reset the MAC address of the XBO: Settings > network > Advanced settings > Alternate mac address > Clear

Peter Pfister
Help Desk Coordinator
414.277.7202

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Justin DeLany, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/1664
Needs IMAP/POP settings to set up Outlook on his personal computer.
Where sorry that you experiencing problems with your email folders. One of limitation of POP/IMAP protocols is that it can't sync folders. It is limited to sending and receiving.
In order for the folders to be synced the email account must be re-added and set up to use exchange. This can be done through outlook in file menu, add account. If you using a Mac here is our exchange setup guide. http://www.msoe.edu/docs/DOC-3869. If necessary the mail server address we use is outlook.office365.com. If you have any issues please let us know.
Thanks, MSOE Information Technology Cameron Wilson 414-277-7288 helpdesk@msoe.edu
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Justin DeLany,

Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/1664
Needs IMAP/POP settings to set up Outlook on his personal computer.

Where sorry that you experiencing problems with your email folders. One of limitation of POP/IMAP protocols is that it can't sync folders. It is limited to sending and receiving. 

In order for the folders to be synced the email account must be re-added and set up to use exchange. This can be done through outlook in file menu, add account. If you using a Mac here is our exchange setup guide.  http://www.msoe.edu/docs/DOC-3869. If necessary the mail server address we use is outlook.office365.com. If you have any issues please let us know.



Thanks,
MSOE Information Technology
Cameron Wilson

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Fw: Your MSOE account password is going to expire soon!
helpdesk-ticket.description:
I'm assuming that other people might be getting this phis-mail. This is the second one of these that I've gotten.
Ed Griggs
Mathematics
________________________________ From: fimservice@msoe.edu <fimservice@msoe.edu> Sent: Tuesday, October 6, 2015 1:00 AM To: Griggs, Edward Subject: Your MSOE account password is going to expire soon!
Edward -
The password for your MSOE account (griggs@msoe.edu) is scheduled to expire on 10/12/2015.
It is highly recommended to change the password for this account prior to 10/12/2015 to avoid any disruption in access. If you do not change the password before the expiration date, access to MSOE systems will be disabled.
Log on to the MSOE password reset portal at https://pwd.msoe.edu and reset your password using the security questions previously provided.
If you have not yet registered for the MSOE password reset portal, go to http://pwdreg.msoe.edu and complete the registration process prior to changing your password.
Your new password must meet the following criteria:
* Passwords must be at least 8 characters
* Passwords must include at least 3 out of these 4 items:
o Uppercase letter
o Lowercase letter
o A number
o A symbol
Note:
The previous four passwords are remembered by the system, so you will need to use a unique password each time your password changes.
Please contact the Help Desk (414-277-7288) if you have any questions or problems resetting your password.
No MSOE employees nor any MSOE correspondence will ever ask you for your account password.
Thank you!

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi meier, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/1678
Dr. Meier would like to be contacted on how to use Web X to setup an online meeting.
Hi Dr. Meier,
There are a few routes to schedule a webex meeting but they all start at meeting.msoe.edu. If you go there and log in with your msoe email address and username you will be on the cwms server. From there you can start, schedule or join a meeting with the buttons on the page.
If you click downloads near the top and right of the page you can download the tools which will integrate webex into outlook so you can schedule meetings in there with the webex server. There is also a desktop app you can download that will allow you some shortcuts from the taskbar.
If you need more info just call me at x7407 and we can talk through it or schedule a time to get the software setup.
Tony

helpdesk-note.body:
Can't the Box folder simply be shared with the people who need access to it?
We'd recommend sharing the folder to the individuals that need access and setting up the users as contributors/editors/owners/viewers, etc. Box was designed with this use in mind, and creating an additional email address will require logging the individual out of single sign-on and then logging in with a shared password of a generic account to Box. We try to stay away from generic accounts, and disrupting all single sing-on accounts to access a Box folder would probably prove frustrating for the users.
Returning to Tier 1. Please contact myself or Mike with questions.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: email
helpdesk-ticket.description:
I had to change my MSOE password after 90 days, and when I changed it, my email on my computer wont update. I have to use the web version on it. How could I fix this problem?
Thank You,
Mitchell Larson
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
I had to change my MSOE password after 90 days, and when I changed it, my email on my computer wont update. I have to use the web version on it. How could I fix this problem?

Thank You,
Mitchell Larson

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Mitchell Larson,
This issue can be fixed by using the credential manager to remove any and all old outlook passwords. I have copy and pasted the instructions from https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/kb/2762344.
"
Click Start, click Control Panel, and then click Credential Manager. Note If View by is set to Category, click User Accounts first, and then click Credential Manager. Locate the set of credentials that has Outlook in the name. Click the name to expand the set of credentials, and then click Remove from Vault. Repeat step 3 for any additional sets of credentials that have the word Outlook in the name.
"
Please let me know if you have success using these instructions or if you need any further assistance. Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/1703

helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Mitchell Larson,

This issue can be fixed by using the credential manager to remove any and all old outlook passwords. I have copy and pasted the instructions from https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/kb/2762344.

"
  1. Click Start, click Control Panel, and then click Credential Manager.

    Note If View by is set to Category, click User Accounts first, and then click Credential Manager.
  2. Locate the set of credentials that has Outlook in the name.
  3. Click the name to expand the set of credentials, and then click Remove from Vault.
  4. Repeat step 3 for any additional sets of credentials that have the word Outlook in the name.
"

Please let me know if you have success using these instructions or if you need any further assistance.

helpdesk-note.body:
In the time frame of the initial creation of this ticket, I was already working on another ticket for her. Just for the record she had told me that the problem fixed itself but fluctuates from working to not working. I left the ticket open because of this.
Moving forward now...
She has always had licensing issues due to her very spotty wifi in her office. That is were her initial problems grew from. She then proceeded to uninstalling the program and re-installing it. (not the right fix) I have worked with matlab all throughout the summer installing/uninstalling it countless times and when on a computer if you uninstall it and reinstall it so many times a problem will occur from overlapping file paths, (items with same file name). Her best bet of having a clean working matlab is to re-image her computer then throw matlab on it.
I will look up a fix for her error. I will call her and talk to her about what are options from here are.

helpdesk-note.body:
Here are two links. I would do both. First deactivate her license and then uninstall the software. After that do a fresh install of Matlab. If that doesn't work re-imaging her laptop will definitely fix the problem.
http://www.mathworks.com/help/install/ug/deactivating-a-license.html
http://www.mathworks.com/help/install/ug/remove-uninstall-mathworks-products.html?s_tid=srchtitle

helpdesk-note.body:
The report I shall give of the tale of my computer woes will in no short measure exult the staff members I worked with yesterday who were without doubt exceptionally helpful and capable.
The tragically confusing and fearful beast born of the malfunctioning machine which I had brought before them required arduous systematic trouble-shooting yet was resolved with highly professional and patient attention to detail. Specifically the support technician I worked with most closely for the duration of the resolution demonstrated not only mastery of hardware and software understanding but also superb customer service, and optimistic humor which made the otherwise traumatic recurrence of the fatal "blue screen of death" (which I have always imminently feared) endurable as I cowered in confusion at the atrocious self-destruction of the machine I had once seen as my friend.
Alas the madden become a knight/princess in shining computer competence vanquished the demon-machine with the help of her fellowship of warrior keyboard-wielders and bid me good tidings as I rode off into the sunset of the early afternoon with more than a new friendly hard drive at my side.
If ever I see a harried traveler or pilgrim with such a threat I will tell them this tale and send them to the sure source of their sorrow’s remission by the skilled craft of those brave protectors of technology. To them I owe many thanks.
